summaries.short: Quick! Someone pass Messy the tissues. He discovers that things just don't taste the same when he has a cold, especially his favourite chewy green socks - let's find out why!
summaries.full: Messy is feeling sorry for himself. “Don’t like colds” he groans and guzzles down a green sock. “Why does food taste different when I have a cold?” Messy goes to Okido to find out. It’s a hot day in Okido so they all go to Lolly’s ice cream van where she explains that there is something strange happening - the flavour you expect doesn’t taste like it should! Zim explains taste buds detect if the food we eat is sweet, sour, bitter or salty. They hear a whirr and a splat so they rush to find a robot who is mixing the wrong ice cream flavours into the pipes. Just like “when our noses are blocked we can’t taste properly” agrees Zoe. Back in the real world Messy seems to be over the worst of his cold and spots another green sock he guzzles is down “it tastes like a green sock. Yum!” he smiles.

summaries.short: Red balloons and blue balloons whatever their colour Messy loves them all – But what's inside them to make them float up high into the sky?
summaries.full: Messy tries to catch a red balloon as it floats past him! “Why do some balloons float but others don’t?” He goes to Okido to find out. In OKIDO Messy, Zoe and Felix see an enormous shimmering bunch of balloons in preparation for a ceremony. Messy starts running towards them and before Felix and Zoe can stop him Messy has done the worst. The bunch of ceremonial balloons become unfixed and rise into the sky. Zim, Zam and Zoom tell them “If you need balloons that float you’ll be needing HELIUM filled balloons!” In ‘The Valley of the Lost Balloons’ they spot the bunch from the playground where Messy takes a giant leap and catches them! Back in the real world Messy admits that he doesn’t mind if his balloons don’t float as helium balloons are a little bit too hard to keep hold of!

summaries.short: The sky is full of big grey rain clouds in the real world. Messy watches his sandcastle outside get washed away by the pouring rain. Why does it have to rain? He competes in the Okido flower competition and finds out why!
summaries.full: Messy is watching the rain pour onto the sandcastle he built earlier and it begins to melt. “Why does it have to rain?” sighs Messy so he goes to OKIDO to find out. Zoe and Felix show Messy their beautiful sunflowers before the City in Bloom competition that afternoon but their sunflowers have wilted under the OKIDO heat and look very sad. Zam explains that plants need three things to keep healthy: sunlight, air and water. They need to find a cloud so they go and find Fluff the raincloud. She collects water droplets from the air until she’s ready to rain onto the sunflowers to help them spring back to life. The Mayor declares Zoe and Felix the winners. Back home, Messy looks out of the window happy to see the rain. “Rain is brilliant. It keeps plants healthy.

summaries.short: Captain Messy is playing pirates with his toys in a bowl of water "the seven seas", but why does his rubber duck float instead of sink?
summaries.full: Messy is in the garden playing ‘float or sink’. But why do some objects sink whilst others float? He goes to Okido to find out. In Okido, Zoe and Felix invite Messy on a boat trip to see the whales of Okido who gather only once every year. Felix has packed a picnic and they all go to a nearby desert island to have a bite to eat. Messy starts to dig for buried treasure! But Messy has unhinged a huge boulder. It begins to roll down the hill, through the picnic and crashes into the boat which sinks. “We have to build a brand new boat!” says Zam and instructs Felix, Zoe and Messy to find some good building materials. They go to gather some wood and Zoom morphs into a hammer to nail the boat together. Suddenly the whales appear. “Seeing those whales was better than any treasure,” says Messy.

summaries.short: Messy monster hears a chirping song bird outside his window but he can't understand what the bird is saying. He goes to OKIDO to find out why all things can't just simply talk the same!
summaries.full: Messy hears a noisy bird outside his bedroom window but he doesn’t understand what the bird is saying and so he goes to OKIDO to find out why. In Okido Felix has lost his voice on the day when Zoe and Felix are to sing a song at the farm festival so they start looking in places where Felix’s voice may be hiding. Zim, Zam and Zoom teach them that you can lose your voice through catching a cold, shouting and that everyone’s voice boxes and vocal chords are slightly different, which is why we all have different voices. They make a ‘Make the voice come back sooner machine’ so Zoe and Felix sing at the farm festival “Old Mac Donald had a farm”. At home Messy looks outside his window and talks to the bird “Hello, Birdie. I know why you sing now. It’s the way you birds talk to each other!”

summaries.short: Messy is having fun blowing loud notes through his musical horn instrument "PARP PARP!!" But whatever noise Messy is making someone or something is making it too. Messy goes in search of the copycat voice.
summaries.full: Messy is playing his horn. PARP he sounds through a play tunnel but he hears the sound repeat back to him. That’s strange? So he goes to OKIDO to find out what it is. There, Zam and Zoom request their help at the lab. They keep hearing a high pitched sound but they can’t find where it’s coming from. Zoe catches sight of something. “A bat!” They learn that bats make clicking noises to send sound waves which hit objects and echo back to them. This helps to tell them the shape and size of things as they fly. At the bat’s cave Zoe and Felix search deeper inside the cave. “Did you hear that?” said Felix “It said what I said. I think what you heard was an echo!” The Cloudship lands back in OKIDO and Messy goes back home “So it wasn’t an invisible person after all. It’s my echo” he grins.

summaries.short: Uh Oh! Messy monster has accidentally dropped his auper stacked jam sandwich snack - But why did it fall down and not up? He goes to OKIDO and rockets up to the moon to find out
summaries.full: Messy is making a jam sandwich but drops it on the floor! “Why do things fall down and not up?” he wonders. In Okido, Messy joins Zoe and Felix who are stargazing up at the night sky. They spot a shooting star which lands in front of them and reveals a baby moonrock! The friends want to help the moonrock find its way home, so they ask Zim, Zam and Zoom who tell them it came from the Moon! Messy and his friends travel in a rocket to get the moonrock safely home. They float inside the rocket, but when they land on the Moon they bounce instead of walk! Zim Zam and Zoom explain that this change is to do with gravity which is different on Earth, in space and on the moon. Back at home, Messy flicks his sandwich into the air! “Now we know why things fall down and not up! That’s gravity!”
